------------
Version 4.1:
------------
@{JLEFT}
- Localebug fixed
- Bug on the Textfields fixed
- Added Config-Loading when Config has been changed

------------
Version 4.0:
------------
- Supports now the Owner.Data protection
- PlugIn-Port added (see Developerdocs for more Informations)
- Objectsmenu removed. Added 4th entry (Off) to position
  cyclegadget Instead
- Chargerproject stopped and to isdnmon added
- If the Lamp.mcc is not available IsdnMon will not quit anymore
- When IsdnMon will be started a 2nd time, it will give you now
  more options :)
- Soundnotification added
- AsciiImport improved: CT (see Importfile for more info)
- Auto-Disconnect added
- Some other enhancements
	- Perform Disconnection (on/off)
	- Keep Number in Textfield (on/off)


-------------
Version 3.20:
-------------
- Bugfix: WindowPositioning failed
- Moved 'Open resizewindow'-Button from Main-Settings to Gui-Settings
- Some clean-up
- Changed 'DisConnect'-PullDownMenu. Only when a Unit is connected
  it is possible to select that item.
- Changed from 'Disconnect Unit...' to 'Disconnect [Name...]'
- At Programstart, IsdnMon checks if Lamp.mcc is existing in 
  MUI:Libs/mui/  
- When Settings are changed and the Position-Window is opened the
  changed settings will not be lost anymore.
- Chargesettings and printing fixed
- When different Prefs are loaded, they will take effect now
- Chargebar added. Here you can see how many time is left, until
  the chargecounter will count one up
- Added possibility to change the CPS to Bps
- Made some optimations. IsdnMon should take less CPU-Time from now on
- Added ENV-Var 'VMC_DEVICE' When you set this var with the device
  you want to use (e.g. vmcisdn0.device) IsdnMon will use that device
  and you do not need to specify the device anymore as parameterstring
  or ToolType
- Enforcerhit fixed at startup
- Bug fixed at RXBytes-Field
- TimerBug fixed
- Keyfile included
  Restriction are: - No Chargebar
		   - Window opens always at upper left corner
		   - Only Unit0 will be monitored
		   - Outgoing MSN will not be displayed
		   - No ArexxPort
		   - IsdnMon will quit after 5 Minutes
- The PositionWindow doesn't work :( -> Fixed
- Amount and Currency can be entered in the Catalogfile
- Some cosmetic changes done
- IsdnMon can be displayed vertical

------------
Version 3.0:
------------
- Some bugfixes
- Removed BSC-Support, because too old, and too buggy.
- Guide added :)
- Added RexxCommands:
	TXBYTES [Unit]       -> Returns the transmitted Bytes
	RXBYTES [Unit]       -> Returns the received Bytes 
	GETONLINETIME [Unit] -> Returns the Time, how long the
				unit is already online (in secs)
	GETCURRENCY [Unit]   -> Returns the currency for the connection

------------
Version 2.0:
------------
- Flickering at Number-, and Costsfield fixed
- Bug: When Titles for Textfields were off, nothing is printed than
  to the Fields (Only at Unit 0)
- Format in the Timefield changed, was: '0: 4: 1' would be now '00:04:01'
- Labels for Units can now be placed (Left/Center/Right)
- Added  CPS  Fields.  Those CPS-Fields will show the complete CPS for the
  whole transmission.
- While filetransfer the clock counts now
- Fixed very lame bug with the ResizeWindow.  Now it has its name back and
  predefined sizes..
- When bscisdn.device is open and connect, IsdnMon crashed when started ->
  Fixed!
- Added Gadgets for Sizing and Positioning
- Added ToolType/DosParameter:
  DEVICE: here you can specify the Device.  Currently you can only specify
          vmcisdnX.device.  If you specify no device, the bscisdn.device
          will be taken.
  AREXXPORTNAME:  Here you can specify the Name of the Public ArexxPort
                  (Default is rexx_ISDNMON) usefull, when you want to have
                  more than one
  CONFIGFILE:  Here you can select a different Configfile.  Also usefull
               when you are using more isdnmons
- At Iconify as Icon, the Icon of IsdnMon will be taken
- The seperator (i.e. '.' or ',') can be changed
- CPS can now be shown as complete for the whole connection or for each
  second
- Disconnecting added
- Enforcerhits removed
- ArexxPort Added (rexx_ISDNMON):
   QUIT -> Quits the Program
   DISCONNECT [n] -> Disconnects the Unit n
   ISCARRIER [n] -> Checks the Carrier on Unit n and returns
                    CARRIER or NO CARRIER
   ISNUMBER [n]  -> Returs the Number with which Number the Unit
                    is connected, No Connection or Number Unknown
- IsdnMon tells you know, when you trying to use an older Version
  of the vmcisdnX.device (2.96)
- Some sanitychecks added
- Added DosParameter ND=NODEBUG.  Hides all DebugOutput (Only in
  BetaVersions!)
- Lamps added: B1, B2, RTS, CTS, Voice
- Added IsdnInfo-Window.  There you can get additional informations
  about a connect (ConnectNumber, ConnectMSN, Protocoll, Speed and
  onlinetimes)


-------------
Version 1.16:
-------------
- Window - Resizing and Repositioning completly changed!
- Labels should not be changed thru textfields anymore

*** Does someone want to write a Doc? Please mail me :) ***


-------------
Version 1.14:
-------------
@{JLEFT}
- Each Unit can be labeled now!
- Fix BorderBug, you can give the IsdnMon a border.
- You can set window's position.  BUT NOTE:  WHEN YOU ALREADY FIXED THE
  POSITION OF YOUR WINDOW, DELETE THE MUIPREFS IN ENV TO MAKE NEW POSITIONS!
  ALSO CHANGE IT IN MUI-PREFS AT 'CONTROL' TO 'FORGET WINDOWPOSITION AT END'
- Fixed Timerfield
- Made some changes to the Transfer-Fields
- Made somechanges to Prefsfile

------------
Version 1.8:
------------
- Added Titles for Lamps and Textfields. Note, the font for the lamps
  is the 'Small Font'. Configurable in MuiSettings (Switchable)
- Shows now MSN's (Switchable)
- When Windowchanges are made, the window will change after saving the
  prefs
- Little Bug fixed in Prefs
- Added Lamp.mcc to Archive
- Added 'Online'-Textfield
- TitleBar for Units removed
- All Windowcontents are switchable


------------
Version 1.0:
------------
- Firsts release


@ENDNODE

